### 6. International Examples of Government Environmental Leadership

| Country        | Key Initiatives & Outcomes                                                                                   |
|----------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| **Sweden**     | High recycling rates through citizen awareness and waste-to-energy plants; imports waste to fuel energy.      |
| **Japan**      | Rigorous waste separation into multiple categories; Kamikatsu aims for 100% recycling by 2020.                |
| **Netherlands**| Use of recycled plastics in infrastructure; strong commitment to renewable energy and circular economy.       |
| **Canada**     | Circular economy culture; innovative recycling of tires and cigarette butts.                                 |
| **Wales**      | Increased recycling from 5% to 64% in 20 years through ambitious policies aiming for zero waste by 2050.      |

These examples illustrate the effectiveness of comprehensive government policies combined with public participation ([OpenMind](https://www.bbvaopenmind.com/en/articles/5-recycling-lessons-from-different-countries-in-the-world/)).

